:"14px","display":"flex","gap":"8px","flexWrap":"wrap"},"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"card-tag before","children":"$$43,920 RECOVERABLE"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"card-tag after","children":"ACTIVE FOLLOW-UP"}]]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block","id":"pain","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"What AR neglect actually looks like"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"You already know the feeling of seeing <em>production on paper but not cash in the bank.</em>"}}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"monologue fade-in","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"","children":"It is the end of the month. The production number looks reasonable. The schedule was full. Your providers worked hard. And yet the deposit does not match what should have come in."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"","children":"You pull the AR report. There is a 90-day bucket that has been growing for three months. There are claims from payers your team has been meaning to follow up with. There are payments that came in at the wrong amount that nobody has had time to dispute."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"highlight","children":"\"Uncollected AR is not a sign your team is doing nothing. It is a sign your team is doing everything — and AR follow-up is always the task that loses to the more urgent thing in front of it.\""}],["$","p","3",{"className":"","children":"Every week that passes without active follow-up, the claims in your aging buckets become harder to collect. Some will cross a timely filing threshold. Some will go to voicemail indefinitely. And some will quietly become write-offs nobody consciously chose to make."}]]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block block--warm","id":"pain-details","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"Why AR stays uncollected"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Seven reasons claims age <em>instead of getting paid.</em>"}}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-ledger fade-in","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"01"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"No one is assigned to specific aging buckets"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When every claim is everyone's responsibility, every claim is also nobody's priority. Without assigned ownership, follow-up happens when time allows — which is never systematic enough to move the needle on aging accounts."}]]}]]}],["$","div","02",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"02"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Payer portals are not checked on a consistent schedule"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Checking claim status across five different payer portals takes more time than the team has on any given day. So status checks happen when someone gets to it — not on a schedule that keeps claims from aging."}]]}]]}],["$","div","03",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"03"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Follow-up notes are vague and impossible to act on"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Someone calls a payer and writes \"called — waiting.\" Three weeks later, nobody knows what was discussed, what was promised, or whether the next step ever happened. Vague notes produce vague follow-up."}]]}]]}],["$","div","04",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"04"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Underpayments are posted and silently accepted"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A payer posts $184 on a claim with a contracted rate of $248. Someone applies it and moves on. Nobody flags the difference. Over months, those small underpayments add up to a significant sum the practice never consciously agreed to write off."}]]}]]}],["$","div","05",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"05"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Difficult payers are deprioritized in favor of easier ones"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Certain payers are harder to reach, slower to respond, and more complicated to escalate with. Without deliberate prioritization, claims from those payers naturally drift to the back of the queue — and stay there."}]]}]]}],["$","div","06",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"06"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Write-offs are applied based on age, not actual collectibility"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When a claim reaches 150 or 180 days, the default is to write it off. But age alone is not a collectibility indicator. Many old claims are still fully recoverable. Without a review, those write-offs are premature."}]]}]]}],["$","div","07",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"07"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Cash flow visibility comes too late to act"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"By the time leadership sees an AR aging report that shows 90-day balances growing, the ideal follow-up window on many of those claims has already started closing. Reactive visibility produces reactive decisions — usually too late."}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}],"$undefined",["$","section",null,{"className":"block block--ink","id":"solution","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"The solution"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display display--light","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"We treat your AR as the revenue it already is. <em>And then we go get it.</em>"}}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Hired Billing Support becomes your dedicated AR management team — assigned to your claims, working in your system, communicating with payers every day, and turning outstanding receivables into actual deposits."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"two-col fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-list","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"01"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"We assign ownership to every aging bucket"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Every claim is assigned to a specific team member with defined follow-up intervals and escalation triggers. Nothing ages without someone watching it and taking the next action."}]]}]]}],["$","div","02",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"02"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"We work payers proactively — before claims get old"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Status is checked on a systematic schedule. Payers are called before the silence becomes a delay. Every interaction is documented with the rep's name, date, and what was committed to."}]]}]]}],["$","div","03",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"03"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"We escalate when standard follow-up is not moving the claim"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Stuck claims do not just sit. We follow payer-specific escalation paths — supervisor requests, formal reconsiderations, and state-level dispute processes when the situation warrants it."}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"process-list","children":[["$","div","04",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"04"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"We flag underpayments before they become write-offs"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Every payment reviewed against contracted rates. Underpayments identified, documented, and pursued through the correct payer process — not silently applied and forgotten."}]]}]]}],["$","div","05",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"05"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"We review write-off eligibility — every time"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"No balance written off without a documented collectibility review. We evaluate whether the claim is recoverable, attempt recovery, and document the rationale before a write-off is ever applied."}]]}]]}],["$","div","06",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"06"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"We report on movement, not just balances"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Your leadership sees what changed — which claims moved, which were collected, which were escalated. Not just a snapshot. A story of what happened to your revenue this month."}]]}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block","id":"services","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"AR management services"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Every piece of the AR workflow. <em>Assigned, tracked, and worked.</em>"}}],["$","p",null,{"children":"$undefined"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"services-grid fade-in","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"service-item","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"service-num","children":"01"}],["$","h4",null,{"children":"Claim Status Tracking"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Regular status checks across payer portals and clearinghouses — on a defined sched